[0m[49m[39m  539, 478[0m:[39m[49m **Where it struggles:**
[0m[49m[39m  540, 479[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 541     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Large anatomical changes between scans (post-surgical, significant weight change)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 542     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Organs with independent motion (bowel, bladder filling differences)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 543     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Very low-resolution source modalities (SPECT) aligned to high-resolution targets
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 544     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Regions with no structural correspondence (air-filled cavities that changed shape)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 545     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - Patient motion during acquisition creating intra-scan inconsistencies
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Severe patient motion between modality acquisitions (>10mm displacement)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Large temporal gaps where anatomy has genuinely changed (tumor growth between scans)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Very low-resolution PET fused with high-resolution MRI (the PET contribution becomes spatially ambiguous)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Post-surgical anatomy where normal anatomical landmarks are absent or distorted
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Metal artifacts in CT (dental implants, surgical hardware) that corrupt the registration metric
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Pediatric patients where body proportions differ significantly from adult training data
